            . I live in <placeName id="t18300415-226-crimeloc1254">Playhouse-yard, Whitecross-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-226-crimeloc1254" type="placeName" value="Playhouse-yard, Whitecross-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-226-crimeloc1254" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-226-off1252 t18300415-226-crimeloc1254"></join>; I rent the shop and parlour of Mr. Fisher, who lives in the house. On the 8th of March I went out about ten o'clock in the evening, and returned about ten minutes after ten; my little girl, who I had left, at home, brought me the key - as I went home I saw the prisoner come out of the house with a bundle under his arm; I took hold of him, and asked what he had got there - he made no answer; I called an officer, gave him in charge, and found the articles stated in the indictment upon him; I had seen them safe that evening - I found my back parlour shutters had been opened and the sash thrown up.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. Have you made inquiries about him? A. A gentleman called and stated that he bore a good character; he appeared in great distress, and I understand had just returned from the East Indies.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>GUILTY (of stealing.) Aged 19. - <rs id="t18300415-226-verdict1255" type="verdictDescription">
